article_title: Centene Clears Big Antitrust Hurdle As Aetna And Anthem Sweat

article_metadata.description: Amid unprecedented health insurance industry consolidation, Centene's $6B purchase of Health Net is the first of three major deals to be approved by federal and state regulators. Still to be approved is Anthem's bid for Cigna and Aetna's takeover of Humana amid intense antitrust scrutiny of health plans
article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen
